!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

location /ləʊˈkeɪʃən/

(locations) 

1. N-COUNT A location is the place where something happens or is situated. 地点 

例： The first thing he looked at was his office's location. 他首先看的是他办公室的位置。 

2. N-COUNT The location of someone or something is their exact position. 准确位置 

例： She knew the exact location of The Eagle's headquarters. 她知道“飞鹰”总部的准确位置。 

3. N-VAR A location is a place away from a studio where a film or part of a film is made. 外景拍摄地 

例： ...an art film with dozens of exotic locations. …一部含有许多异国外景的艺术电影。

</div>

